headline: How Investors May Respond To Intercontinental Exchange (ICE) Record Highs in Global Futures Open Interest
summary: Intercontinental Exchange recently reported that its global futures and options markets reached a record open interest of 107.6 million contracts, marking substantial year-over-year growth across commodities, energy, and natural gas segments. This surge highlights increasing trust in ICE’s liquidity and benchmarks, reflecting strong customer participation amid evolving market demands.
